title: Wybejong Park Riddells Creek Flora And Fauna

items.title: Suta flagellum
items.content_text: Found under tin at Wybejong Park working bee. Record and photo by Lyn Hovey. First record of this species in Riddells Creek.

items.title: Austroagrion watsoni
items.content_text: Mating.

items.title: Orthetrum caledonicum
items.content_text: Shows wing colouration. Male.

items.title: Ischnura heterosticta heterosticta
items.content_text: Male.

items.title: Austroagrion watsoni
items.content_text: Male.

items.title: Sceliphron laetum
items.content_text: The size of this wasp took me by surprise when it flew by - a very large wasp.

items.title: Vanessa kershawi
items.content_text: In what I think is Mentha X piperita (weed).

items.title: Austroagrion watsoni
items.content_text: Male.

items.title: Ornduffia reniformis
items.content_text: Also a male Austroagrion watsoni sitting on a leaf in pic2.

items.title: Austrolestes leda
items.content_text: Male 'guarding' female as she lays eggs on Triglochin procera s.l.. New species record for Riddells Creek (no. 21). 11th species recorded at Wybejong.

items.title: Phalaenoides glycinae
items.content_text: Feeding in planted Westringia.

items.title: Ischnura aurora
items.content_text: Tiny damselfly. New species record for Riddells Creek.

items.title: Cordulephya pygmaea
items.content_text: Autumn flying dragonfly. Rests with wings held shut.

items.title: Mentha X piperita, Pieris rapae rapae
items.content_text: Leaves petiolate and 9cm x 3cm further down the stem.

items.title: Myriophyllum crispatum
items.content_text: Leaves terete in upper 90% of plant with a few lobed leaves at base. Leaves 6-whorled. Buds fusiform.

items.title: Hemicordulia australiae
items.content_text: Mating pair. New species record for Riddells Creek.

items.title: Acrida conica
items.content_text: Very large grasshopper. Seen heaps this year for the first time on the grassland rail reserves but never been able to get close to one (very flighty).

items.title: Ischnura heterosticta heterosticta
items.content_text: Two spots on back of the head is a distinguishing feature for this species.

items.title: Diplacodes bipunctata
items.content_text: Flying in a dried up, rocky creek bed along with male D. haematodes and male O. caledonicum among other species.

items.title: Ocybadistes walkeri sothis
items.content_text: Different individuals in the two pics.

items.title: Cordulephya pygmaea
items.content_text: Tiny dragonfly (a true dragonfly with the wings held together - like a damselfly). A new species record for Riddells Creek.

items.title: Orthetrum caledonicum
items.content_text: I saw this dragonfly tucking into what looks like a fly or bee (looks a bit like a Cuckoo Bee). No females observed.

items.title: Diplacodes haematodes
items.content_text: New species record for Riddells Creek. 2nd & 3rd pic shows yellowish colouring on proximal half of wing - an ID feature for this species. No females seen.

items.title: Elatine gratioloides
items.content_text: Seems to be a new species record for the Macedon Range. On the northern creekside at Wybejong Park.

items.title: Persicaria decipiens, Zizina labradus labradus
items.content_text: Lots flying around the Persicaria on the creekside.

items.title: Heteronympha penelope penelope
items.content_text: I think landed on some old Yorkshire Fog.

items.title: Geitoneura acantha
items.content_text: Females, like this one, are much larger compared to males.
